Bug 1740: Modification for LSS:
StationControl accepts the optional key 'ObservationControl.LSSscript' in the parameter set. If this key exists and is not empty and the mentioned script exists and is executable and the antennaSet is LBA_OUTER THEN the script is executed with the name of the parset as he first and only argument when an CONTROL_CONNECT events comes by.

The script should scp the parset file to the LSS_LCU and start some LSS specific software on that machine.

ObservationControl is modified to be able to start an observation without the MACScheduler, it (also) accepts 1 argument being the name of the parset in /opt/lofar/share.
Note: in automatic mode the invocation is with 3 arguments.

rspctl and beamctl have a new option '--remotehost <hostname>' to execute the command on another machine than the current.

